<span class="pageTitle">Information We Collect</span><br/>
<br/>
<strong>Registration and Your Account Information</strong>
<p>
Personal information means information that can be used to identify and contact you. You do not need to submit personal information to access certain areas of the Site, but if you do not want to disclose certain personal information to us, you will not be able to access certain aspects of the Services. 
</p>
<p>
When you register with the Site, we require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, such as your email address, name, title, date of birth, mailing address and telephone number. If you are registering for a corporate account with Allopass, you will also be required to provide your company name, mailing address, fax and telephone numbers, and the title, name and email address of the company contact. When registering for an individual or corporate account, you will also select a password. Your email address and password will be used so you can securely access and maintain your account. 
</p>
<p>
We may also require you to provide your Federal Tax ID, IRS W-9 form information and/or any other tax verification information so we can make payments to you and comply with relevant tax laws. If you elect to receive payments from the Services in the form of a wire transfer, you will also be required to provide your bank account information. 
</p>
<br/><br/>
<strong>Customer Service</strong>
<p>
We provide customer service support through email. In order to provide customer support, we will ask for your email address and telephone number. Aside from this information, we do not ask for any personal information to provide customer support. We only use information received from customer support requests, including email addresses, for customer support services and we do not transfer or share this information with any third parties. 
</p>
<strong>Cookies</strong>
<p>
Like many websites, we employ "cookies" in certain areas of the Site to allow us to make your online experience more convenient and to limit fraud. Cookies are small bits of electronic information that a website sends to a visitor's browser and are stored on the visitor's hard drive. Each user is assigned a “cookie ID” from our Site domain in connection with the registration process. We use cookies, including your cookie ID, for the following purposes: 
</p>
<ul>
<li>o store a user's log-in identity and password and automatically populate the log-in fields for you when you re-access the Site; </li>
<li>to monitor irregular account behavior and implement fraud protection rules; and </li>
<li>to generate and compile anonymous, aggregated statistics that allow us to understand how users navigate our site and to help us improve it.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
You may refuse the use of cookies by selecting the appropriate settings on your browser; however, if you do this, you may not be able to use the full functionality of the Site or Services. 
</p>
<br/><br/>

<strong>Log Information </strong>
<p>
Our servers automatically record information that your browser sends whenever you visit the Site. This information includes your Internet Protocol address, your cookie ID, which Services you use and when and how long you use them and otherwise access the Site. We use this information to provide customer service and to maintain and improve the Services. 
</p>
<br/><br/>

<strong>How We Use Your Information</strong>
<p>
As a general matter, we use the information that you provide to us to process your user registration, and to provide, enhance and personalize the Site and Services. We use the information automatically collected by our servers to monitor and analyze how users use the Site and Services, and to maintain and improve the Site and Services. 
We may use your email address and/or phone number for the following purposes: 
</p>
<ul>
<li>
<li>to send you other email communications that keep you updated about Services and other functionality of the Site, including, monthly updates regarding available upgrades, Service functionality and/or features; </li>
<li>to respond to or confirm your requests or activity on the Site, including password retrieval; </li>
